elements.title: Willy von Beckerath
elements.contents: ... that Willy von Beckerath, after studying at the Kunstakademie Düsseldorf, depicted Johannes Brahms at a grand piano (pictured)?

elements.title: CSS Maurepas
elements.contents: ... that the original name of the sidewheel steamer CSS Maurepas, Grosse Tete, means "big head" in French?

elements.title: Osman Çakmak
elements.contents: ... that Osman Çakmak won the European Amputee Football Championship as a player in 2017 and as a manager in 2021 with the Turkey national team?

elements.title: Sutton 58
elements.contents: ... that after plans for the skyscraper Sutton 58 prompted a height limit for the surrounding area, construction went ahead anyway?

elements.title: Fort Raim
elements.contents: ... that the Russian Fort Raim was built in 1847 around the ruined mausoleum of Kazakh warrior Raiymbek Batyr?

elements.title: Sherita Hill Golden
elements.contents: ... that Sherita Hill Golden demonstrated that diabetics were more likely to develop depression and that those with depression were more likely to become diabetic?

elements.title: Say You to Yo Asobi
elements.contents: ... that the Japanese variety show Say You to Yo Asobi collaborated with the Japan Racing Association to create a special video about the Takarazuka Kinen horse race?

elements.title: Bonifasius Belawan Geh
elements.contents: ... that prior to entering politics, Bonifasius Belawan Geh collected edible bird's nests from the jungle after dropping out of college?
